com.hcl.domino.json

Interface JsonDeserializer


  • public interface JsonDeserializer
    This interface allows for deserialization of JSON into documents, both as strings and as implementation-specific Java object representations.

    Implementations of this service are expected to be provided by additional integration modules, such as domino-jnx-jsonp.

    Since:
    1.0.9
    Author:
    Jesse Gallagher

      • target

        Parameters:

        Returns:
        this deserializer

      • dateTimeItems

        JsonDeserializer dateTimeItems(Collection<String> dateTimeItems)
        Configures the deserializer to expect the named items to contain date/time values.

        This will cause such values to be parsed as date/times and ranges compatible with the output of JsonSerializer and to throw an exception when the value in the incoming JSON object is not either a valid value or empty.

        Parameters:
        dateTimeItems - the names of items expected to contain date/time values
        Returns:
        this deserializer

      • removeMissingItems

        JsonDeserializer removeMissingItems(boolean removeMissingItems)
        Configures whether items in a document provided via target(Document) that do not exist in the incoming JSON should be removed.

        The default behavior is to only update items that are represented as properties in the incoming JSON.

        The "Form" item and items beginning with "$" will never be removed in this way.

        Parameters:
        removeMissingItems - whether items not present in JSON should be removed
        Returns:
        this deserializer

      • booleanValues

        Parameters:

        falseValue - the value used when converting false
        Returns:
